1	//axhob_operation
2	{rbtgo_image_retrieve}
3	
4	NOTE: This operation wrests a container image from
5	{rbtgi_repository}
6	to the local container runtime.
7	
8	`rbfl_wrest` is locator-generic: the same procedure pulls
9	{rbtga_ark}
10	hallmark members,
11	reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.
12	The package path embedded in the
13	{rbst_locator}
14	selects the domain — the procedure itself does not branch.
15	
16	NOTE: This is a {rbtr_director} operation (Director credentials, registry write/admin tier — same authority as {rbtgo_image_delete}). It is not the {rbtr_retriever}-tier counterpart of {rbtgo_ark_summon}: summon performs vouch ceremony before pulling under retriever credentials, while wrest is a direct pull with no vouch and no health classification. Use wrest for diagnostic or development pulls; use summon for production retrieval.
17	
18	The
19	{rbtr_director}
20	wrests an image by {rbst_locator}:
21	
22	//axhopt_typed_parameter
23	{rbst_locator}
24	. *Validate Input Parameters*:
25	.. {rbbc_require}
26	`«INPUT_LOCATOR»` provided as first argument in `package-path:tag` format
27	.. {rbbc_fatal}
28	if missing: "Locator parameter required (package-path:tag)"
29	.. {rbbc_fatal}
30	if malformed (no colon): "Invalid locator format. Expected package-path:tag"
31	.. {rbbc_store}
32	`«PACKAGE_PATH»` as portion before the final colon (e.g., `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/image`, `{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/«STAMP»/syft`, `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/«ANCHOR»`)
33	.. {rbbc_store}
34	`«TAG»` as portion after the final colon
35	.. {rbbc_fatal}
36	if `«PACKAGE_PATH»` is empty: "Package path is empty in locator"
37	.. {rbbc_fatal}
38	if `«TAG»` is empty: "Tag is empty in locator"
39	
40	//axhos_step
41	. *Authenticate as
42	{rbtr_director}*:
43	.. Execute
44	{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
45	.. {rbbc_store}
46	`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent operations
47	
48	//axhos_step
49	. *Construct Registry Reference*:
50	.. {rbbc_store}
51	`«REGISTRY_HOST»` as `{rbrd_gcp_region}-docker.pkg.dev`
52	.. {rbbc_store}
53	`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
54	.. {rbbc_store}
55	`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
56	.. {rbbc_store}
57	`«FULL_IMAGE_REF»` as `«REGISTRY_HOST»/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/«GAR_REPOSITORY»/«INPUT_LOCATOR»`
58	
59	//axhos_step
60	. *Configure Container Runtime Authentication*:
61	.. {rbbc_call}
62	container runtime login with:
63	... registry: `«REGISTRY_HOST»`
64	... username: `oauth2accesstoken`
65	... password: `«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
66	.. {rbbc_require}
67	login successful
68	.. {rbbc_fatal}
69	if login fails: "Container runtime authentication failed"
70	
71	//axhos_step
72	. *Pull Image*:
73	.. {rbbc_call}
74	link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#pulling-manifests[Docker Registry API: pull] via container runtime:
75	... command: `docker pull «FULL_IMAGE_REF»` or `podman pull «FULL_IMAGE_REF»`
76	.. {rbbc_require}
77	pull completes successfully
78	.. {rbbc_store}
79	`«IMAGE_ID»` from pulled image metadata
80	.. {rbbc_fatal}
81	if pull fails: "Image pull failed"
82	
83	//axhoot_typed_output
84	{rbtgi_image}
85	. *Display Results*:
86	.. {rbbc_show}
87	image wrested: `«FULL_IMAGE_REF»`
88	.. {rbbc_show}
89	local image ID: `«IMAGE_ID»`
90	
91	//axhoc_completion
92	Successful execution wrests the image and displays the local image ID.
93	The locator-generic shape means a hallmark member, a reliquary tool image, or an enshrinement image are all retrieved by the same call — domain identity lives in the locator's package path, not in branched logic.
